        }
      ],
      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">A 65-year-old male with a history of atrial fibrillation presents for a routine cardiology follow-up. His medication adherence is confirmed, and he remains asymptomatic. During the visit, his cardiologist discusses the patient&#39;s cardiac conduction system, explaining how impulses travel through various structures at different velocities. </span></span><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">What will be the conduction velocity of the structure marked (red arrow) in the picture (cardiac conduction system)?</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cerebellum-web-static.s3.amazonaws.com/media/public/images/2024/03/08/19.jpg\" style=\"height:369px; width:300px\" /></span></span></p>",
      "unique_key": "Q9084189",
      "question_audio": null,
      "question_video": null,
      "map_id": 33364,
      "difficulty_level": "intermediate",
      "subjects_id": [
        2
      ],
      "solution": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Ans. C) 1 m/s</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Option&nbsp;</span></strong><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">C.&nbsp;</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">The marked structure is <strong>Bundle of His</strong> and its <strong>velocity is 1 m/s</strong>.&nbsp; The <strong>conduction velocity</strong> of 1 m/s is characteristic of the <strong>bundle branches</strong>, which are responsible for quickly directing the <strong>electrical activity</strong> from the <strong>AV node</strong> to the <strong>ventricles&#39; Purkinje fibers</strong>.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><u><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Explanation</span></u></strong><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">:</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Option&nbsp;</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><strong>A.</strong>&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><strong>Incorrect</strong>. A conduction velocity of <strong>0.05 m/s is too slow</strong> for the cardiac conduction system, especially for the bundle branches which are designed to rapidly conduct electrical impulses towards the ventricles.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Option&nbsp;</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><strong>B.</strong>&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><strong>Incorrect</strong>. While <strong>faster than 0.05 m/s</strong>, a velocity of <strong>0.5 m/s</strong> is still not representative of the rapid conduction through the bundle branches; it is closer to the conduction velocity in the atria.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Option&nbsp;</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><strong>D.</strong>&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><strong>Incorrect</strong>. A conduction velocity of <strong>4 m/s is too fast</strong> and is not characteristic of the cardiac conduction system; it exceeds the known velocities for any part of the system.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><u><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Educational Objective:</span></u></strong><u> </u></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Recognize</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"> the typical <strong>conduction velocity</strong> of the <strong>bundle branches</strong> in the <strong>cardiac conduction system</strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cerebellum-web-static.s3.amazonaws.com/media/public/images/2024/02/29/screenshot-2024-02-28-120720.jpg\" style=\"height:452px; width:700px\" /></strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><u><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Refer</span></u></strong><strong><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">: Ganong&rsquo;s Review of Medical Physiology, 25<sup>th</sup> Edition, Pg No: 522)</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>",
