          "id": 31235,
          "text": "<p><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">1,2,3,4</span></span></p>"
        }
      ],
      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">A 70-year-old male with a history of chronic heart failure is admitted to the cardiology unit due to worsening exertional dyspnea. The medical team is monitoring his cardiac function closely, including oxygen consumption, to optimize his treatment regimen. Which of the following is involved in determining the oxygen consumption by the heart?</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n\t<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Myocardial contraction</span></span></span></li>\r\n\t<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Heart rate</span></span></span></li>\r\n\t<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Myocardial tension</span></span></span></li>\r\n\t<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Blood flow</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ol>",
      "unique_key": "Q5395776",
      "question_audio": null,
      "question_video": null,
      "map_id": 33360,
      "difficulty_level": "intermediate",
      "subjects_id": [
        2
      ],
      "solution": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Ans. D) 1,2,3,4</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><strong>Option D.</strong> &nbsp;<strong>Myocardial oxygen consumption</strong> is determined by a combination of factors including <strong>myocardial contraction, heart rate</strong> (which increases the frequency of contractions), <strong>myocardial tension</strong> (related to ventricular pressure and volume), and <strong>blood flow</strong> (which supplies oxygen). The interplay of these factors <strong>dictates the metabolic demands of the heart</strong>.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><u><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Explanation</span></u></strong><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">:</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><strong>Option A.</strong> <strong>Incorrect</strong>. While <strong>myocardial contraction is a significant determinant of oxygen consumption</strong>, it is not the sole factor. Other elements such as heart rate, myocardial tension, and blood flow also play crucial roles.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><strong>Option B.</strong> <strong>Incorrect</strong>. Myocardial contraction and tension are important, but this option <strong>overlooks the impact of heart rate and coronary blood flow</strong>, both of which are critical in meeting the metabolic demands of the heart.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><strong>Option C.</strong> <strong>Incorrect</strong>. Although <strong>myocardial contraction, tension, and blood flow are significant</strong>, this option does not <strong>account for heart rate</strong>, which directly influences myocardial oxygen demand by affecting the number of contractions per minute.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><u><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Educational Objective:</span></u></strong><u> </u></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Recognize that myocardial oxygen consumption is influenced by multiple factors including <strong>myocardial contraction, heart rate, myocardial tension, and blood flow</strong>, each contributing to the overall metabolic demand of the heart.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><u><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Refer</span></u></strong><strong><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">: Ganong&rsquo;s Review of Medical physiology, 25<sup>th</sup> edition, pg no: 550</span></strong></span></span></p>",
